<!--
                Used for game macros
               	--------------------
Tags:
-----
       NAME:	just the name of the macro..

       KEY:		the name of the keyboard key  associated to the macro(use names like space, backspace,esc, 
				enter,ins, home, page_up, page_down, end, up, down,
				left, right, F1, F2,...
				or simply characters like a,b,c for characters keys)
       
       LEFT_SHIFT:		set 1 if you want the key to be pressed with right shift at the same time

       RIGHT_SHIFT,
       LEFT_CONTROL,
       RIGHT_CONTROL,
       LEFT_ALT,
       RIGHT_ALT:		same as above

       SCRIPT_FUNCTION:	the name of the CSL function (usually in macros.csl, but could be everywhere) to be executed 
                        when the macro key is pressed.

       PARAMETER:	you can add up-to 4 parameters to be passed to the function. You must specify the parameter
					type with the attribute TYPE(for example PARAMETER TYPE="string". Legal values for type
					are only "string" and "integer"

	   Note:		name attribute in parameter is not important, i used it just to let macros be more readable.
-->

